for arrangements involving multiple elements  we allocate revenue to each component based on the vendor specific objective evidence of the fair value of the various elements 
these elements may include two or more of the following software licenses  maintenance and support  consulting services and training 
for arrangements where vendor specific objective evidence is not available for a delivered element  we first allocate the arrangement fee to the undelivered elements based on the total fair value of those undelivered elements  as indicated by vendor specific objective evidence 
this portion of the arrangement fee is deferred 
then the difference residual between the total arrangement fee and the amount deferred for the undelivered elements is recognized as revenue related to the delivered elements 
we attribute the discount offered in a multiple element arrangement entirely to the delivered elements of the transaction  which are typically software licenses 
fair values for the future maintenance and support services are based upon substantially similar sales of renewals of maintenance and support contracts to other customers 
fair value of future services  training or consulting services is based upon substantially similar sales of these services to other customers 
